OL,3,CCharities 'dismayed and frustrated' at
OL,4,CStormont's Anti-Poverty Strategy
OL,6,FLaunching the strategy earlier this
OL,7,Fmonth, Mr Lyons described it as being
OL,8,Fbased on three pillars of minimising
OL,9,Frisks of falling into poverty,
OL,10,Fminimising the impact of poverty on
OL,11,Fpeople's lives and working to help
OL,12,Fpeople get out of poverty.
OL,14,FFigures indicated that around 18% of
OL,15,Fpeople in Northern Ireland live in
OL,16,Frelative poverty, and 15% live in
OL,17,Fabsolute poverty, with 25% of children
OL,18,Fin relative poverty and 21% of
OL,19,Fchildren in absolute poverty.
